 and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Keynes was born in 1266, in Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Keynes, was 34 and his mother, Mrs Maud De Keynes of Milton Keynes, was 31. He married Alice in 1291, in Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1295, in Shalstone, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 29."},"et":{"1266–1295":"1266–1295","1255–Male":"1255–Surnud","1270–1295":"1270–1295","1292–1315":"1292–1315","1233–1283":"1233–1283","1236–Female":"1236–Surnud","about 1260":"umbes 1260","about 1292":"umbes 1292","Bef 10 January 1283":"enne 10. jaanuari 1283","1295":"1295","1283":"1283","1292":"1292","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","1315":"1315","1236":"1236","1266":"1266","1233":"1233","1255":"1255","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Shalstone, Buckinghamshire, England":"Shalstone, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, , England":"Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1266–1295":"1266–1295","1255–Male":"1255–Kuollut","1270–1295":"1270–1295","1292–1315":"1292–1315","1233–1283":"1233–1283","1236–Female":"1236–Kuollut","about 1260":"noin 1260","abo